            . On Saturday the 7th of December, between six and seven o'clock in the evening, I was going from the city towards Salisbury-court in <placeName id="t17550116-15-crimeloc81">Fleet-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17550116-15-crimeloc81" type="placeName" value="Fleet-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17550116-15-crimeloc81" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17550116-15-off79 t17550116-15-crimeloc81"></join>, this boy at the bar came jostling against me, I immediately clapped my hand in my pocket and found my handkerchief was gone; I took him by the wrist and went into a hosier's shop facing Bridewell-lane; when I came to the light I perceived my handkerchief up his sleeve, I took it out (produced in court and deposed to) he said another boy threw it over his shoulder and ran away.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you perceive any other boy near you?</p>
               <p>B. Gray. No, I saw none but the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>Two boys got me to take a walk with them, one of them took that handkerchief and put it up my arm and ran away.</p>
